<br>
1. GREED BEFORE NEED - Works best in pick-up groups, every item is up for grabs by the whole group. It has the benefit of avoiding any ambiguity over who really needs an item - but it is important to state the rule in advance.<br>
<br>
2. RAN 100 - The most common use of this is that everyone in the group rolls just once and the highest roll gets first pick of the loot, second highest gets second pick etc. This can save an awful lot of rolling about <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
3. If there is only one really valuable item up for roll, the group leader can assign a number between 0 and 5 for each group member. The leader then rolls /ran 6.<br>
<br>
4. NEED BEFORE GREED - is often very tricky. One suggestion I have made before and has been well received by the groups I was in, is that if a person is claiming NBG then the item which the loot replaces is the included for the rest of the group to roll on. For example, if someone has a Skyfire sword and wants to claim NBG on a Crystalline Short Sword then the Skyfire is put up for grabs by th rest of the group. This goes some way to ensuring that someone who is claiming NBG is REALLY in need of it.<br>
